For a demonstration, go here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.nadiar.com/levels/xpcalc.php">www.nadiar.com/levels/xpcalc.php</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Mob level is going to play a significant role. What level are the PoP mobs?<br>
75?<br>
<br>
Then the XP given right now is equal to:<br>
Solo Formula:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>75^2 * 145 * 3.9 * (50+5/ (50+5*1)*1)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Duo Formula:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>75^2 * 145 * 3.9 * (50+5/ (100+5*2)*1.02)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Mob level * Mob Level * ZEM * Difficulty level * ((Your Level + 5)/(Your total group level + 5(your group number) * Group Number Modifier).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Now, where am I going you may be asking? AA XP is Regular XP divided by 1.25.<br>
<br>
So lets work backwards on this.<br>
<br>
Currently, 1 Quad in Fire gives you 70% (17.5% per)<br>
On test they are reporting that 1 Quad in Fire gives you 44% (11% per)<br>
Each AA is 15,000,000 xp.<br>
17.5% is 2,625,000 xp<br>
11% is 1,650,000 xp.<br>
<br>
OLD WAY:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2,625,000 * 1.25 = 3,281,250 / ZEM(3.9*75*75) = 3,281,250 /  (21,937.5*ZEM) = 150<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
(which just means someone was over-estimating, but okay)<br>
<br>
<br>
NEW WAY:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1,650,000 * 1.25 = 2,062,500 / ZEM(3.9*75*75) = 2,062,500 / (21,937.5*ZEM)<br>
94.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Going to make a guess here and say that they wouldn't want SSra to be better xp than the Planes, which means the Planes are going to be a 100ZEM.<br>
<br>
Which means that SOLO you make xp just like you were soloing in SSra, The Hole, or Old Cazic Thule.<br>
<br>
So, lets look at an Old Group of 65's vs. a new group of 65's in PoP, killing a level 63 creature (like in Valor)<br>
OLD WAY:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>63^2 * 145 * 2.34 * (65+5/ (390+5*6)*1.2) = 1,346,681.7 * 0.2= 269,336 (which is 1.44% AA per kill)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
NEW WAY:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>63^2 * 100 * 2.34 * (65+5/ (325+5*5)*1.8)  = 928,746 * (1.8 * 70/350) = 928,746 * 2 = 334,348 1.78% AA per kill<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Which means overall yield in a full group will go up by approximately 24% per kill.<br>
<br>
This is using your numbers Valael, but feel free to recheck my math. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8991"><br>
